      "side": 1,
      "message": "Maybe this should CHECK() instead of hoping that the -1 bubbles up to where it has to go.\n\n(On POSIX, exit codes are weird, because main() returns int, and exit() accepts int, but usually only 8 bits are visible to other processes. So I’m not really talking about our own care in propagating the exit code as much as I’m thinking about the OS handling.)",
