      "writtenOn": "2018-01-23T19:42:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed, it was filed as US-408, which resulted in https://fuchsia-review.googlesource.com/c/garnet/+/108305, but that only affects appmgr launched binaries... and it would actually make things worse if it affected `namespace` because it hardcodes argv[0] to \"/pkg/bin/app\", rather than the real name of the binary. (I\u0027m not sure sure why it\u0027s called \"arv0\" in the code either.)\n\nIt seems Fuchsia really doesn\u0027t want us to know anything about our binary name or where it is on the file system or if it\u0027s even on a file system. Which seems nice in theory, but impractical in non-final-deployment situations. I\u0027ll follow up on the bug anyway.",
      "parentUuid": "6c311397_24bf769d",
